com.salesforce.omakase.util

Interface Equivalents.EquivalentWalker<P,N extends Named>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - (P)eer. See Equivalents.prefixes(Object, Named, EquivalentWalker) for more details.
    N - (N)amed unit. See Equivalents.prefixes(Object, Named, EquivalentWalker) for more details.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Equivalents.AtRuleBase, Equivalents.Base, Equivalents.RuleBase
    Enclosing class:
    Equivalents

    public static interface Equivalents.EquivalentWalker<P,N extends Named>
    Responsible for finding the next and previous "peers", and also for determining whether a "peer" is an prefixed equivalent.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      N locate(P peer, N unprefixed)
      Returns the named unit that is prefixed-equivalent within/of the given peer, or null if the given peer is not prefixed-equivalent.
      P next(P peer)
      Gets the next unit, or null if none.
      P previous(P peer)
      Gets the previous unit, or null if none.
      boolean walkAll()
      Specifies whether we should walk all peers, or stop when a peer does not match.

    • Method Detail

      • walkAll

        boolean walkAll()
        Specifies whether we should walk all peers, or stop when a peer does not match.

        In other words, return true to evaluate all peers, even when null is returned from locate(Object, Named), and return false to stop walking (in that direction) once locate(Object, Named) returns null.

        Returns:
        Whether all peers should be walked, or if we should stop walking a direction once a peer does not match.
